# ToolBite — Cursor Permanent Rules

## Dark Mode (MANDATORY)
Every Tailwind class that sets color MUST include both light and dark variants.
Never write a color class without its dark counterpart.

### Backgrounds
- bg-white → bg-white dark:bg-gray-800
- bg-gray-50 → bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-700
- bg-gray-100 → bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-700
- bg-indigo-50 → bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-900/30
- bg-blue-50 → bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/30
- bg-green-50 → bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/30
- bg-red-50 → bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/30

### Icon Wrapper Backgrounds (Tool Cards)
- bg-indigo-100 → bg-indigo-100 dark:bg-indigo-900/40
- bg-blue-100 → bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-900/40
- bg-green-100 → bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/40
- bg-yellow-100 → bg-yellow-100 dark:bg-yellow-900/40
- bg-red-100 → bg-red-100 dark:bg-red-900/40
- bg-purple-100 → bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-900/40
- bg-pink-100 → bg-pink-100 dark:bg-pink-900/40
- bg-orange-100 → bg-orange-100 dark:bg-orange-900/40
- bg-teal-100 → bg-teal-100 dark:bg-teal-900/40
- bg-cyan-100 → bg-cyan-100 dark:bg-cyan-900/40
- bg-rose-100 → bg-rose-100 dark:bg-rose-900/40
- bg-violet-100 → bg-violet-100 dark:bg-violet-900/40
- bg-emerald-100 → bg-emerald-100 dark:bg-emerald-900/40
- bg-amber-100 → bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900/40
- bg-lime-100 → bg-lime-100 dark:bg-lime-900/40
- bg-sky-100 → bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900/40

### Text
- text-gray-900 → text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100
- text-gray-800 → text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200
- text-gray-700 → text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300
- text-gray-600 → text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400
- text-gray-500 → text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400

### Icon Text Colors (Tool Cards)
- text-indigo-600 → text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400
- text-blue-600 → text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400
- text-green-600 → text-green-600 dark:text-green-400
- text-yellow-600 → text-yellow-600 dark:text-yellow-400
- text-red-600 → text-red-600 dark:text-red-400
- text-purple-600 → text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400
- text-pink-600 → text-pink-600 dark:text-pink-400
- text-orange-600 → text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400
- text-teal-600 → text-teal-600 dark:text-teal-400
- text-cyan-600 → text-cyan-600 dark:text-cyan-400
- text-rose-600 → text-rose-600 dark:text-rose-400
- text-violet-600 → text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400
- text-emerald-600 → text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400
- text-amber-600 → text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400
- text-sky-600 → text-sky-600 dark:text-sky-400

### Borders
- border-gray-100 → border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-700
- border-gray-200 → border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-600
- border-gray-300 → border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600

### Hover States
- hover:bg-gray-50 → hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-700
- hover:bg-indigo-50 → hover:bg-indigo-50 dark:hover:bg-indigo-900/30
- hover:border-indigo-200 → hover:border-indigo-200 dark:hover:border-indigo-700
- hover:border-blue-200 → hover:border-blue-200 dark:hover:border-blue-700

### Shadows
- shadow-xl → shadow-xl dark:shadow-gray-900/50
- shadow-md → shadow-md dark:shadow-gray-900/40
- shadow-sm → shadow-sm dark:shadow-gray-900/30

## Component Standards (MANDATORY)
- Cards: always use .tb-card or .tb-card--hover from global.css
- Buttons: always use .tb-btn + .tb-btn--primary / --secondary / --ghost
- NO inline Tailwind for new cards or buttons

## Meta Descriptions (MANDATORY)
- Every new HTML page must have a unique meta description
- Length: exactly 150-160 characters
- Must describe the specific page content, no generic phrases

## SEO (MANDATORY)
- Every new page needs: title, meta description, canonical link
- Heading hierarchy: one H1 per page, then H2, H3 in order
- All images: alt, width, height, loading="lazy"

## JavaScript (MANDATORY)
- No console.log statements in production code
- Theme toggle must use data-theme="dark"/"light" on <html> element
- No localStorage or sessionStorage usage

## Git (MANDATORY)
- Never commit: .DS_Store, seo-meta-descriptions.csv, *.log
- Commit messages format: type: short description
  Types: feat / fix / seo / style / refactor / docs
